2. "Commercial Offering" means any product, service, subscription, hosted service, managed service, paid feature, paid plan, license, bundle, consulting engagement, or other offering in which payment or other monetary consideration is required, directly or indirectly, to obtain access to, receive, operate, or use all or part of the Software.

3. "Direct Infrastructure Costs" means actual and reasonable third party charges that are directly attributable to hosting or delivering the Software. These costs are limited to compute, storage, bandwidth, container registry charges, payment processing fees, and mandatory taxes. Direct Infrastructure Costs do not include labor, installation, support, administration, monitoring, management, development, maintenance, depreciation, general overhead, profit, or markup.

4. "Copyright Holder" means Cenodude, or any legal successor that owns the relevant copyright in the Software.

