## 5. Hosted Containers and Cost Recovery

You may distribute the Software through a container image, or provide a hosted container deployment running the Software, while charging only for Direct Infrastructure Costs.

Any charge under this Section must:

1. Be limited to the actual Direct Infrastructure Costs attributable to the relevant user or deployment.

2. Contain no profit, markup, labor charge, support charge, management charge, administrative charge, or general overhead allocation.

3. Be reasonably itemized and capable of being substantiated by records of the underlying costs.

4. Not be bundled with paid features, paid support, paid management, or any other Commercial Offering.

5. Not imply that any amount is being charged for the Software itself.

This cost recovery exception does not remove any notice or distribution requirement under this License.

